using namespace std;

namespace kindergarten_garden {

    vector<string> plants(const string& diagram, const string& child) {
        // Split the diagram into rows by newline
        vector<string> rows;
        istringstream iss(diagram);
        string line;
        while (getline(iss, line)) {
            if (!line.empty()) {
                rows.push_back(line);
            }
        }
        
        // Ensure we have exactly two rows
        if (rows.size() != 2) {
            // Handle error case, but according to instructions, it should always be two rows
            return {};
        }
        
        const string& row1 = rows[0];
        const string& row2 = rows[1];
        
        // List of children in order
        vector<string> children = {
            "Alice", "Bob", "Charlie", "David",
            "Eve", "Fred", "Ginny", "Harriet",
            "Ileana", "Joseph", "Kincaid", "Larry"
        };
        
        // Find the index of the child
        int index = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < children.size(); i++) {
            if (children[i] == child) {
                index = i;
                break;
            }
        }
        
        // If child not found, return empty vector
        if (index == -1) {
            return {};
        }
        
        // Each child has 2 plants per row, so their plants are at 2*index and 2*index +1
        int start_pos = 2 * index;
        
        // Get the plant codes
        vector<char> plant_codes;
        plant_codes.push_back(row1[start_pos]);
        plant_codes.push_back(row1[start_pos + 1]);
        plant_codes.push_back(row2[start_pos]);
        plant_codes.push_back(row2[start_pos + 1]);
        
        // Convert to plant names
        vector<string> result;
        for (char code : plant_codes) {
            switch (code) {
                case 'G': result.push_back("grass"); break;
                case 'C': result.push_back("clover"); break;
                case 'R': result.push_back("radishes"); break;
                case 'V': result.push_back("violets"); break;
                default: result.push_back(""); // Handle unexpected codes if necessary
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
